race.description: Goulburn Post Country Boosted Mdn Handicap
race.comment: Tricky. ROSE DIAMOND (2) has been unlucky not to have broken through and will be having her first full preparation for the Kelley stable. She placed at Cranbourne for the Hayes stable at her only fresh outing, and she sets a decent standard. MEDEIA (7) is a local on debut, and the Seib yard is flying. She's sure to be more effective than the trial finishes suggest, and 33% stable-striker Boudvillain sticks from those. SMOLENSKI (5) is another local and resumes gelding off a soft trial. Has a low gate, and Collett is a key jockey engagement. Likely to lead and race well. MARITIME EXPRESS (1) resumes and has switched from the Seib stable. Has a wide gate to contend with, but Heywood was aboard in her most recent trial and is on today. The gelding was backed off the map when placing here on debut, and has to be kept very safe.
